                    "description": "Title: \"Computational Modelling of the Coastal Protection Function of Salt Marshes with Flexible Vegetation Cover\"\nSummary: Salt marshes are intertidal wetlands that can serve as natural coastal protection. I studied the interaction between vegetation, currents and flow and sediment through experiments and computational modelling (Delft3D, SWAN).  I developed a new module to include the effect of vegetation flexibility, which was successfully applied to a real world case study. Part of NERC-funded CoastWEB.\nTasks: Hydrodynamic modelling, physical experiments, data analysis, independent research, academic writing, publishing in peer-reviewed journals.\nSupervisors: Prof. Dr. H.U. Karunarathna and Prof. Dr. D.E. Reeve",
